Here you can read the difference: https://sass-lang.com/documentation/at-rules/control/for

&gt; [...] If **to** is used, the final number is excluded; if **through** is used,
&gt; it&#39;s included.

Then, when you use `through`:

    @for $i from 1 through 3{
      div{
        content:$i;
      }
    }

you create this output:

    div {
      content: 1;
    }
    
    div {
      content: 2;
    }
    
    div {
      content: 3;
    }


Instead, using `to`:

    @for $i from 1 to 3{
      div{
        content:$i;
      }
    }

You create this output:

    div {
      content: 1;
    }
    
    div {
      content: 2;
    }

